				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Hellfire Campaigns: The Universe at Your Feet" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>This guide is written to help you fight wargames campaigns. The guide is written to help both the player with enthusiastic opponents but also to support the solo player as well.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Although written with Hellfire rules in mind, a lot of the campaign systems will work comfortably with any rule system you like. The rest will be be easily modifiable to cope with whatever rules or figure scale you want to use. The rules will cope with a wide variety of periods as well.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;I confess that I've always regarded the wargames campaign to be wargaming at its finest. Done properly a campaign can provide far more interesting and unexpected games than just facing an equal points army across the table. This guide is written in an attempt to ensure that you manage to extract the maximum amount of fun whilst limiting the book-keeping. Whether you want to use massed heavy armour, or ride the fleeing enemy infantry down with your wild horsemen, this rule set will help you make sure it's all done in a suitably cost-efficient manner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Combat accountancy has never been a particular love of mine and I'd hate to impose it on anybody else.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer / publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
